1
00:00:06,139 --> 00:00:08,630
<i>You had Vic arrested?</i>

2
00:00:08,808 --> 00:00:13,575
<i>- I just filed a complaint.
- Well, he's spending the night
in jail right now.</i>

3
00:00:13,780 --> 00:00:16,271
<i>- I can't even bail him out till the morning.
- He broke into my house.</i>

4
00:00:16,449 --> 00:00:20,715
Oh, come on. He worked his ass off
to pay for this house, Corrine.

5
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:23,584
<i>- What are you thinking?
- My kids are sleeping. Good night.</i>

6
00:00:23,723 --> 00:00:27,090
<i>- I really need for his head
to be in the game right now.
- Then go tell him.</i>

7
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:29,851
<i>He's worried about you, and that kind
of distraction can get him killed.</i>

8
00:00:30,030 --> 00:00:32,498
<i>- Me and the other guys too.
- That's not my fault.</i>

9
00:00:32,665 --> 00:00:35,201
Go home, Shane.

10
00:00:35,236 --> 00:00:40,036
<i>Would you just back off?
Just leave him...Just leave him alone!</i>

11
00:00:42,675 --> 00:00:44,472
- What were you thinking?
- Hey, where I come from...

12
00:00:44,677 --> 00:00:46,440
when a guy's lady jams him up,
his buddies have a talk with her.

13
00:00:46,679 --> 00:00:49,149
- Not in the middle of the night, Jethro.
- I'm sorry.

14
00:00:49,184 --> 00:00:51,049
But you need to be able
to concentrate right now.

15
00:00:51,151 --> 00:00:54,279
- Are you okay?
- Where are we with the money train?

16
00:00:54,821 --> 00:00:57,221
- It's definitely pulling out tonight.
- What's the new collection point?

17
00:00:57,390 --> 00:00:59,192
Well, we don't know yet.

18
00:00:59,227 --> 00:01:01,820
What about the guy who ran
the last site, shut it down?

19
00:01:02,262 --> 00:01:05,060
- We ran his plates. Got an address.
- His name's Chorekian.

20
00:01:05,231 --> 00:01:08,689
- He's the advance man.
- Follow him. Maybe he'll
take us to the new site.

21
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:12,136
Took us two months to scout the last site.
You want to do this one in a few hours?

22
00:01:12,472 --> 00:01:16,067
We still got the truck, the equipment,
the plans. All that stays the same.

23
00:01:16,109 --> 00:01:18,942
<i>- Might stay the same.
- Never get another chance like this again.</i>

24
00:01:19,279 --> 00:01:22,146
Let's remember where
this Armenian money's coming from...

25
00:01:22,382 --> 00:01:24,543
prostitution, drugs, robberies.

26
00:01:24,684 --> 00:01:27,050
<i>And the rest of this cash is just gonna
finance more of the same.</i>

27
00:01:27,220 --> 00:01:29,711
They didn't earn it.
I don't feel bad about taking it.

28
00:01:29,889 --> 00:01:34,461
<i>We get a little for ourselves,
set the Armenian mob back months.</i>

29
00:01:34,496 --> 00:01:36,895
Ronnie, you gas up the truck,
ready the equipment.

30
00:01:37,330 --> 00:01:40,128
Shane, Lem, you get on
this Armenian advance man.

31
00:01:40,333 --> 00:01:42,460
<i>- See where he takes us.
- All right. Come on.</i>

32
00:01:42,602 --> 00:01:45,435
- David, who'd you vote for?
- I'll give you a hint.

33
00:01:45,638 --> 00:01:47,574
- He's Latino.
- And he's handsome.

34
00:01:47,609 --> 00:01:50,099
<i>Any comment on the report
you recommended the chief fire...</i>

35
00:01:50,543 --> 00:01:53,613
<i>the anti-gang unit you oversee?</i>

36
00:01:53,648 --> 00:01:57,276
I didn't feel they were meeting the high
standards we expect of our officers.

37
00:01:57,884 --> 00:02:01,581
<i>The report also suggests
you offered yourself up as well.</i>

38
00:02:01,754 --> 00:02:05,212
I'm their commanding officer.
They were my responsibility.

39
00:02:05,258 --> 00:02:09,354
If I'm gonna hold them to a high standard,
I should expect the same of myself.

40
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:15,827
Chief Bankston, it's good
to finally meet you.

41
00:02:18,304 --> 00:02:22,638
Captain Aceveda seems to think
your team is a real problem.

42
00:02:22,942 --> 00:02:25,467
He's recommending that I fire you all.

43
00:02:29,182 --> 00:02:32,185
My team is responsible
for more than 50%...

44
00:02:32,220 --> 00:02:34,050
of drug and gang arrests
in that district.

45
00:02:34,687 --> 00:02:38,145
<i>The results are impressive.
It's the methods that have me concerned.</i>

46
00:02:38,258 --> 00:02:42,558
Aceveda and I don't always
see eye to eye on tactics.

47
00:02:42,729 --> 00:02:44,788
<i>Well, that won't be
a problem for long.</i>

48
00:02:44,931 --> 00:02:47,957
After he loses
the primary today, he's resigning.

49
00:02:48,101 --> 00:02:50,865
<i>I don't know what kind of latitude
the last chief gave you...</i>

50
00:02:51,070 --> 00:02:54,301
but I believe in doing things well
and doing them right.

51
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:56,271
So do I.

52
00:02:56,409 --> 00:02:59,242
<i>I know when a cop has
his toe over the line, Detective.</i>

53
00:02:59,512 --> 00:03:03,346
Are you going to be able to maintain your
stellar arrest rate without crossing any lines?

54
00:03:03,550 --> 00:03:06,314
<i>- Absolutely.
- Prove it to me...</i>

55
00:03:06,519 --> 00:03:11,115
or I'll have no problem acting on
your captain's recommendations.

56
00:03:20,266 --> 00:03:22,860
You put my team on the termination list
you gave to the chief?

57
00:03:23,536 --> 00:03:26,733
I don't have time for you.
I've gotta tell 27 people today...

58
00:03:26,839 --> 00:03:28,608
the chief's office
just fired them.

59
00:03:28,643 --> 00:03:32,212
That's right, and I'm not one of them.
You are, aren't you?

60
00:03:32,247 --> 00:03:34,806
Consider yourself
on desk duty for the day.

61
00:03:35,448 --> 00:03:37,951
- Where do you get off trying...
- I heard about your arrest.

62
00:03:37,986 --> 00:03:40,385
Congratulations.
Go clean up your own house...

63
00:03:40,787 --> 00:03:42,584
instead of continuing
to mess up mine.

64
00:03:42,789 --> 00:03:46,350
The chief wants me out making cases,
and that's exactly what I'm gonna do.

65
00:03:46,526 --> 00:03:48,323
- I gave you an order.
- You're a goddamn lame duck.

66
00:03:48,528 --> 00:03:52,692
- An order you'll goddamn follow.
- Or what? You'll recommend that I'm fired?

67
00:03:52,832 --> 00:03:55,528
Been nice knowing you.

68
00:04:06,579 --> 00:04:08,672
<i>Can you read his lips?</i>

69
00:04:08,848 --> 00:04:12,079
<i>Even if I could,
I don't speak Armenian, bro.</i>

70
00:04:12,185 --> 00:04:14,710
That's his third call in the last five blocks.
He's definitely notifying the troops.

71
00:04:14,887 --> 00:04:17,981
<i>All right. He's moving again.
He's moving.</i>

72
00:04:18,124 --> 00:04:20,251
Follow the money.

73
00:04:20,393 --> 00:04:22,691
Let's go.

74
00:04:24,998 --> 00:04:28,559
Claudette, there's been
a homicide on Dresden.

75
00:04:29,135 --> 00:04:32,438
- Great. We're ready to roll.
- No.

76
00:04:32,473 --> 00:04:36,169
- The victim's your ex-husband, Jeff Franklin.
- You're kidding.

77
00:04:36,509 --> 00:04:39,069
Your daughter Bonnie's there.

78
00:04:39,345 --> 00:04:41,404
She's supposed to be
in Florida. Is she okay?

79
00:04:41,447 --> 00:04:43,244
I think so, but she's a witness.

80
00:04:43,449 --> 00:04:47,510
Dutch, you take the case.
You'll have to be limited to observing.

81
00:04:47,687 --> 00:04:49,555
Uh, I've got a personal involvement,
granted a tertiary one.

82
00:04:49,590 --> 00:04:51,318
Shouldn't you hand it off
to Brent or Marlon?

83
00:04:51,524 --> 00:04:54,584
We're gonna be a little shorthanded
today. The case is yours.

84
00:04:55,094 --> 00:04:57,324
<i>- Brent, Marlon.
- Yeah, Captain.</i>

85
00:04:57,463 --> 00:04:59,897
Can I see you
up in my office, please?

86
00:05:00,066 --> 00:05:01,931
Here it comes.

87
00:05:08,574 --> 00:05:11,168
- You ready?
- Not really.

88
00:05:22,021 --> 00:05:26,287
- Mom.
- There's blood. Let me get that for ya.

89
00:05:26,426 --> 00:05:29,486
- He-He shot him.
- I know.

90
00:05:29,629 --> 00:05:31,722
He's gone.

91
00:05:31,864 --> 00:05:34,526
I know, honey.

92
00:05:34,734 --> 00:05:37,294
- You got it.
- I'm sorry, Bonnie.

93
00:05:41,174 --> 00:05:43,642
There's not a single damn witness...
none that we could find...

94
00:05:43,943 --> 00:05:45,843
except the daughter.

95
00:05:46,045 --> 00:05:48,843
- That's Claudette's ex-husband?
- Yeah.

96
00:05:49,048 --> 00:05:52,347
Tell the M.E. to move his ass. I want
the body released as soon as possible.

97
00:05:52,485 --> 00:05:54,316
<i>Gotcha.</i>

98
00:05:58,491 --> 00:06:00,460
Christ, is this guy
on quaaludes?

99
00:06:00,495 --> 00:06:02,894
He don't want to get pulled over.
It's a good sign.

100
00:06:03,463 --> 00:06:06,796
- Means he's close to a go.
- Goddamn it. Get your ass in gear, granny.

101
00:06:11,671 --> 00:06:14,674
Did he just hit him?

102
00:06:14,709 --> 00:06:17,040
I'm sorry. I didn't... I didn't think
you were gonna stop.

103
00:06:17,543 --> 00:06:20,842
- It's goddamn yellow. What's wrong with you?
- No reason to get upset.

104
00:06:21,013 --> 00:06:23,846
No reason for you. You drive a piece
of shit. I just bought this car.

105
00:06:24,016 --> 00:06:27,611
<i>- Relax. I'm covered.
- We're gonna lose the
goddamn money train over this.</i>

106
00:06:27,787 --> 00:06:31,382
- What do we do if...
- I don't know.

107
00:06:31,457 --> 00:06:33,823
<i>- Oh, no way.
- Try getting outta here. Go around the block.</i>

108
00:06:34,127 --> 00:06:36,295
<i>- Shit.
- Cover up.</i>

109
00:06:36,330 --> 00:06:39,787
- You saw him hit me, right?
- Yeah, he rear-ended you, man. It sucks.

110
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:41,930
You be my witness for insurance?

111
00:06:42,135 --> 00:06:46,595
- You would do that?
- Sure. Yeah. I guess I could do that.

112
00:06:46,773 --> 00:06:48,866
- Yeah.
- Give me your number.

113
00:06:51,477 --> 00:06:53,604
You know, I tell you,
I'm always on the road.

114
00:06:53,980 --> 00:06:55,481
Maybe we should just
exchange cell numbers.

115
00:06:55,516 --> 00:06:58,917
- Otherwise, you know, we'll
probably never hook up.
- Yeah. Okay.

116
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:03,589
It's always the ones that don't
give a shit about their cars...

117
00:07:03,624 --> 00:07:06,649
- that run into yours.
- You don't have to tell me.

118
00:07:09,562 --> 00:07:12,087
I'm Armin Chorekian.

119
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:14,699
- Cletis van Damme.
- Thank you for your help.

120
00:07:14,867 --> 00:07:17,495
I call you.

121
00:07:17,703 --> 00:07:19,864
Cletis van Damme?

122
00:07:20,006 --> 00:07:21,741
There's nothing major
going on right now.

123
00:07:21,776 --> 00:07:24,972
Streets are up for grabs, and there's not
one gang case in the last 24 hours...

124
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:27,037
- we can sink our teeth into?
- Sorry.

125
00:07:27,246 --> 00:07:29,840
Hey, what's the rush?

126
00:07:30,049 --> 00:07:31,880
The chief's evaluating our unit.

127
00:07:32,084 --> 00:07:34,678
We have to appear busy
and irreplaceable.

128
00:07:34,854 --> 00:07:37,414
I know Dutch is working
on a homicide from this morning.

129
00:07:37,657 --> 00:07:40,091
I don't know the details.

130
00:07:42,261 --> 00:07:45,560
Uh, Dutch-boy,
what are you workin' on?

131
00:07:45,631 --> 00:07:47,861
Claudette's ex-husband
was shot and killed.

132
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:50,364
Her daughter Bonnie
witnessed the whole thing.

133
00:07:50,503 --> 00:07:52,630
<i>Oh, man. What happened?</i>

134
00:07:52,772 --> 00:07:56,572
They were sitting in a car,
black male walked up, said something...

135
00:07:56,776 --> 00:07:59,142
then just shot the guy
ran away.

136
00:07:59,312 --> 00:08:00,802
<i>- It's a gang thing?
- I don't know...</i>

137
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:03,278
and Bonnie's been
too upset to talk to.

138
00:08:03,416 --> 00:08:05,316
<i>I still don't know
why she and her dad were there.</i>

139
00:08:05,518 --> 00:08:08,282
Let me work the gang angle.
See if there's anything there.

140
00:08:08,521 --> 00:08:12,218
Great. I'll make a copy
of my notes up till now.

141
00:08:14,093 --> 00:08:16,994
If he's in here,
I'll recognize him.

142
00:08:17,230 --> 00:08:19,198
There are a lot of pictures
in there, so take your time.

143
00:08:19,233 --> 00:08:22,463
You need to take a break
to eat, anything, just ask, okay?

144
00:08:22,835 --> 00:08:24,632
Okay.

145
00:08:26,305 --> 00:08:28,808
You do me a favor.
You see him in there, you tell me first.

146
00:08:28,843 --> 00:08:32,710
- Don't say anything to Dutch, okay?
- Why?

147
00:08:32,812 --> 00:08:34,609
Because there are
a lot of ways to make a case...

148
00:08:34,814 --> 00:08:37,977
and being a star eyewitness at a murder trial
doesn't have to be your first option.

149
00:08:38,317 --> 00:08:40,114
Not with the kind of guy
who did this.

150
00:08:40,453 --> 00:08:42,978
- This is Dad we're talking about.
- I know.

151
00:08:43,155 --> 00:08:45,623
I don't care what I have to do.

152
00:08:48,060 --> 00:08:51,427
I know you feel that way right now,
but I'm only watching out for you.

153
00:08:52,064 --> 00:08:53,861
God, Mom.
I can't believe you.

154
00:08:54,133 --> 00:08:57,637
I'm not talking about
letting whoever did this go free.

155
00:08:57,672 --> 00:09:01,232
I just don't want you to get into
something you can't get out of later.

156
00:09:01,474 --> 00:09:04,637
If you see him in there,
you tell me first.

157
00:09:07,613 --> 00:09:09,774
I hear you called Julien's house.

158
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:12,214
Told his little boy
that he was gay?

159
00:09:12,251 --> 00:09:15,354
- I think you got the wrong guys.
- I got the right assholes.

160
00:09:15,389 --> 00:09:18,687
The both of you have been shooting your
mouths off about how much fun you're having.

161
00:09:19,091 --> 00:09:22,527
I got no problem with someone
being gay out there, but in here I...

162
00:09:22,595 --> 00:09:24,358
If it's so cool, why doesn't he just
come out and say it?

163
00:09:24,697 --> 00:09:26,858
Why is he lying
about who he is?

164
00:09:26,999 --> 00:09:29,092
I'm putting you both on notice.

165
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:32,068
Fun's over, or I end it myself.

166
00:09:38,110 --> 00:09:40,169
- Herman, what do you got?
- Something.

167
00:09:40,279 --> 00:09:42,782
But what's in it for my boys?

168
00:09:42,817 --> 00:09:46,411
We lay off that gambling joint
you're running near MacArthur Park.

169
00:09:46,519 --> 00:09:50,148
- What gambling joint?
- The one in the back
of Morty's Sporting Goods.

170
00:09:52,224 --> 00:09:54,988
Oh, that one. Okay.

171
00:09:55,194 --> 00:09:56,762
So you all heard
of the E-ParkJohnnies?

172
00:09:56,797 --> 00:09:59,629
<i>- Not recently. They still kicking around?
- They still breathing.</i>

173
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:04,170
<i>With Armadillo and the Torrucos out
of business, everything is opening up out there.</i>

174
00:10:04,205 --> 00:10:06,035
The Johnnies are looking to get back
on top of the bangers heap.

175
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:08,301
Good luck.

176
00:10:08,474 --> 00:10:11,500
Jesus Christ, Herman, pick that up.
Pick it up!

177
00:10:13,412 --> 00:10:16,245
Hey, sorry, man.
Strictly for medicinal purposes.

178
00:10:17,917 --> 00:10:19,748
So what does the Johnnies
trying to bring back the glory days...

179
00:10:19,919 --> 00:10:21,716
have to do with some dad
getting shot in his car?

180
00:10:22,321 --> 00:10:25,825
All I heard was the Johnnies were bragging
about throwing some kind of April Fool's party.

181
00:10:25,860 --> 00:10:28,453
- April Fool's party?
- Yeah, that's all I heard, man.

182
00:10:29,028 --> 00:10:31,462
<i>- Bonnie.
- Yes?</i>

183
00:10:31,530 --> 00:10:35,227
<i>- Hi, I'm Detective Mackey.
- Hi. Tavon Garris.</i>

184
00:10:35,534 --> 00:10:37,195
<i>- Hi.
- I'm sorry about your father.</i>

185
00:10:37,403 --> 00:10:40,133
- Thank you.
- I just have one question for you.

186
00:10:40,339 --> 00:10:43,775
<i>The shooter...he said something
to your dad before he fired?</i>

187
00:10:43,843 --> 00:10:47,574
<i>Yes. I...I couldn't hear him very well.
The window was up.</i>

188
00:10:47,813 --> 00:10:51,305
<i>Did it sound like,
"Johnny says April Fool's"?</i>

189
00:10:51,584 --> 00:10:54,348
It was something
like that, yeah.

190
00:10:54,553 --> 00:10:58,284
I couldn't hear it clear, but...
What does that mean?

191
00:10:58,491 --> 00:11:00,356
<i>Bonnie?</i>

192
00:11:01,394 --> 00:11:04,693
- What are you doing?
- Answering his questions.

193
00:11:05,131 --> 00:11:07,326
He's not involved in this case.

194
00:11:14,674 --> 00:11:16,676
Look, 10 years ago,
the E-ParkJohnnies...

195
00:11:16,711 --> 00:11:18,701
were the predominant
gang in Farmington.

196
00:11:18,944 --> 00:11:20,946
They controlled drugs,
sex, everything.

197
00:11:20,981 --> 00:11:23,073
Until the Mexicans
started outnumbering them.

198
00:11:23,449 --> 00:11:25,576
Compton gangs started moving in,
squeezed the Johnnies right out.

199
00:11:25,785 --> 00:11:28,754
I talked to my
old partner, Joe Clarke.

200
00:11:28,789 --> 00:11:31,917
He says the E-ParkJohnnies
used to throw what they called
April Fool's parties.

201
00:11:32,391 --> 00:11:34,188
What are those?

202
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:36,862
Every year they tally up how many
members got killed out on the street...

203
00:11:36,897 --> 00:11:39,558
then they get the whole membership
together, and they pick dominoes.

204
00:11:40,066 --> 00:11:42,125
- Dominoes?
- Yeah. You pick the right one...

205
00:11:42,268 --> 00:11:44,036
you get to be one of
the shooters.

206
00:11:44,071 --> 00:11:46,698
- Who'd they shoot?
- Didn't matter. Walk right up to 'em...

207
00:11:46,806 --> 00:11:49,536
<i>and say, "Johnny says April Fool's,"
boom... they'd shoot 'em.</i>

208
00:11:49,809 --> 00:11:53,677
And, uh, that's what your daughter
heard the shooter say this morning.

209
00:11:54,313 --> 00:11:56,440
<i>The April Fool's parties dried up
about 10 years ago...</i>

210
00:11:56,515 --> 00:11:58,278
but looks like
they're back on.

211
00:11:58,484 --> 00:12:01,920
Thanks for the tip.
Dutch'll take care of it.

212
00:12:02,088 --> 00:12:05,455
- Is there a problem with
us helping or something?
- No, it doesn't concern you.

213
00:12:05,624 --> 00:12:07,785
Dutch will take care of it.

214
00:12:13,299 --> 00:12:15,801
Run the gang database for Johnnies
that were killed in the last year...

215
00:12:15,836 --> 00:12:17,598
and get a current address
for their leader.

216
00:12:18,137 --> 00:12:20,162
Uh, street name's Lops.

217
00:12:20,306 --> 00:12:22,408
- Lops?
