Team about how that guy got the knife?

443
00:29:36,374 --> 00:29:39,778
<i>- I've heard the rumors.
- Yeah?</i>

444
00:29:39,813 --> 00:29:43,839
Who's looking into it while my career's
being flushed down the goddamn toilet?

445
00:29:44,182 --> 00:29:47,174
Right now... nobody.

446
00:30:09,874 --> 00:30:11,342
Here's Ronnie.

447
00:30:11,377 --> 00:30:15,472
- He must have heard the shots.
- Ohh, oh, this is not good.

448
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:19,810
- Where is Vic?
- We gotta do this now,
before he's hung out to dry.

449
00:30:20,285 --> 00:30:25,290
Look, I'm gonna take the guy
with the MP-5.

450
00:30:25,325 --> 00:30:28,418
You take the skinny guy with the beanie
and the blowgun.

451
00:30:28,726 --> 00:30:31,092
Come on, man.
We gotta do this now.

452
00:30:34,933 --> 00:30:37,299
On the goddamn ground!

453
00:30:37,869 --> 00:30:40,064
<i>- Get down right now!
- Get down!</i>

454
00:30:40,205 --> 00:30:43,003
Everybody down now!

455
00:30:44,275 --> 00:30:46,675
Get your ass down! Down!

456
00:30:46,845 --> 00:30:49,837
Get on the ground!

457
00:30:49,981 --> 00:30:53,815
Get down! Get down there!

458
00:30:54,018 --> 00:30:55,918
<i>- You good? You clear?
- Clear!</i>

459
00:30:56,120 --> 00:30:58,520
Goddamn it, this guy's hurt.

460
00:30:58,690 --> 00:31:00,885
<i>- Face down!
- Oh, shit. It's the last van.</i>

461
00:31:01,025 --> 00:31:04,620
Guys, don't move,
don't move. Do not...

462
00:31:04,796 --> 00:31:06,696
Okay.

463
00:31:14,339 --> 00:31:17,331
Go. Go get him!

464
00:31:18,743 --> 00:31:20,506
Don't move!

465
00:31:28,353 --> 00:31:31,379
- Stay right there! Hands on the wheel!
- Go, go, go, go, go!

466
00:31:39,163 --> 00:31:41,532
Thank God
you made it, man.

467
00:31:41,567 --> 00:31:44,296
What the hell happened here?
We got dead bodies?

468
00:31:44,903 --> 00:31:47,338
It wasn't us.
They turned on each other.

469
00:31:47,373 --> 00:31:49,636
Ronnie heard the shots.
The whole thing went down a van early.

470
00:31:50,141 --> 00:31:52,041
Jesus!

471
00:31:52,210 --> 00:31:55,646
- We gotta go. If anybody heard those shots...
- We also got a wounded Armenian.

472
00:31:55,914 --> 00:31:58,144
<i>If this guy doesn't get medical help,
he's gonna bleed out and die.</i>

473
00:31:58,383 --> 00:32:00,112
That's not our problem.
We didn't shoot him.

474
00:32:00,251 --> 00:32:01,920
Now let's load up
and get the hell outta here.

475
00:32:01,955 --> 00:32:03,683
<i>Yeah, so we didn't shoot him,
but we can save him.</i>

476
00:32:04,122 --> 00:32:06,181
I don't want that blood
on my conscience.

477
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:12,323
Me either. We better hurry.
Let's go.

478
00:32:20,071 --> 00:32:23,007
- Do you want to live or die?
- Live. Please.

479
00:32:23,042 --> 00:32:27,103
Well, then, you listen
very carefully, Dach.

480
00:32:27,512 --> 00:32:30,310
- We're gonna get you to the doctor.
- Thank you.

481
00:32:30,515 --> 00:32:32,574
Then we're gonna stop by your house
and hide some of this money...

482
00:32:32,717 --> 00:32:35,219
and since you're the only guy
who's gonna be missing from here...

483
00:32:35,254 --> 00:32:39,622
your buddies are gonna figure that we took
care of you because you were our inside man.

484
00:32:40,124 --> 00:32:41,921
They'll come looking for you...

485
00:32:42,026 --> 00:32:44,028
and the only thing they'll find
at your house is their stolen cash.

486
00:32:44,063 --> 00:32:46,223
And then they'll know
you were the one...

487
00:32:46,531 --> 00:32:48,965
who tipped us off
about the money train.

488
00:32:49,267 --> 00:32:53,670
- I don't even know who you are.
- Well, that's gonna be our little secret.

489
00:32:53,771 --> 00:32:58,265
Once you get fixed up, you're running
away, Dach, and never coming back.

490
00:32:58,543 --> 00:33:01,842
Yes. Just get me help, please.

491
00:33:01,980 --> 00:33:05,609
Do you see the man
that shot your father?

492
00:33:20,999 --> 00:33:23,024
- What?
- If this goes to trial...

493
00:33:23,167 --> 00:33:26,534
I don't want Bonnie being a witness...

494
00:33:26,704 --> 00:33:29,195
in a gang killing.

495
00:33:29,374 --> 00:33:31,239
Understand?

496
00:33:36,948 --> 00:33:39,508
Yeah. Yeah, I understand.

497
00:33:53,031 --> 00:33:55,864
If I were to question these men...

498
00:33:57,702 --> 00:34:00,330
any idea who I should
start with first?

499
00:34:09,147 --> 00:34:10,944
I'd start with number two.

500
00:34:14,619 --> 00:34:16,587
<i>You and your two friends...</i>

501
00:34:16,622 --> 00:34:19,954
You all drew the double-three dominoes.
We found one on each of you.

502
00:34:20,091 --> 00:34:22,685
Two of you didn't kill anyone,
but one of you did.

503
00:34:23,261 --> 00:34:25,092
I don't know nothin'
about no killin'.

504
00:34:25,296 --> 00:34:27,821
Okay, we'll see who your two friends
point the finger at...

505
00:34:27,999 --> 00:34:29,830
'cause one of you is going to jail.

506
00:34:30,068 --> 00:34:31,797
<i>Hang up!</i>

507
00:34:32,003 --> 00:34:34,597
I don't want to go to jail
for something I didn't do...

508
00:34:34,772 --> 00:34:38,776
<i>just 'cause one of them
said I did.</i>

509
00:34:38,811 --> 00:34:41,210
Then put someone else there.
I don't care who.

510
00:34:46,517 --> 00:34:49,509
It was Mouser.
He did it.

511
00:34:52,657 --> 00:34:54,454
Hey.

512
00:34:54,659 --> 00:34:57,184
<i>- Make it in time?
- Where?</i>

513
00:34:57,361 --> 00:34:59,522
<i>- Wherever you were going.
- Oh, yeah.</i>

514
00:34:59,664 --> 00:35:02,258
Just an errand.

515
00:35:02,433 --> 00:35:04,492
Got it handled.
No biggie.

516
00:35:04,635 --> 00:35:06,604
Anything happen around here?

517
00:35:06,639 --> 00:35:08,834
We got the other two domino shooters
without any other killings.

518
00:35:09,140 --> 00:35:12,007
- Dutch is upstairs sorting them out.
- Sweet.

519
00:35:12,210 --> 00:35:14,110
Anything else happening?

520
00:35:14,312 --> 00:35:17,804
<i>Nah. Other than that,
it's been quiet.</i>

521
00:35:17,982 --> 00:35:19,973
Good.

522
00:35:21,419 --> 00:35:23,410
- What's up?
- I just got fired.

523
00:35:23,554 --> 00:35:26,955
- What?
- Yeah. My name's on the casualty list.

524
00:35:27,024 --> 00:35:29,515
- Any guesses why?
- Jesus Christ. I'm sorry.

525
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:33,587
You're the one that's always talking about
your boys being such stand-up guys...

526
00:35:33,798 --> 00:35:37,666
You and I both know that my name
doesn't belong on that list.

527
00:35:37,902 --> 00:35:40,894
Let's see how much of
a stand-up guy you really are.

528
00:35:46,777 --> 00:35:49,580
<i>- What?
- You fired Danny?</i>

529
00:35:49,615 --> 00:35:53,209
- The chief's office did.
- She doesn't deserve that.
You got to do something.

530
00:35:53,751 --> 00:35:56,049
Armadillo died because Danny
didn't properly pat down the prisoner.

531
00:35:56,254 --> 00:35:58,916
- Ah...
- Unless you have something
to share with the chief...

532
00:35:59,157 --> 00:36:01,182
this conversation's over.

533
00:36:01,325 --> 00:36:03,816
Do you?
Or are you a coward?

534
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:12,098
Too bad.

535
00:36:12,270 --> 00:36:14,431
She was a good officer.

536
00:36:21,612 --> 00:36:24,672
It was Mouser.
He did it.

537
00:36:27,018 --> 00:36:28,753
Ohh, man!

538
00:36:28,788 --> 00:36:31,381
I can't believe
he'd just give me up like that.

539
00:36:31,856 --> 00:36:35,451
- I didn't do it.
- You ready to give him up?

540
00:36:37,929 --> 00:36:39,794
He killed that man.

541
00:36:39,964 --> 00:36:42,558
He wanted to be the first one
of the three of us.

542
00:36:42,767 --> 00:36:44,530
Real important to him.

543
00:36:44,735 --> 00:36:47,329
How do I know you're the one
telling the truth?

544
00:36:47,505 --> 00:36:51,908
Yo, I fill you in
on where he hides his gun.

545
00:37:01,219 --> 00:37:04,677
- I hear we got the shooters upstairs.
- Looks like it.

546
00:37:06,057 --> 00:37:08,719
Well, not to pat myself
on the back or anything...

547
00:37:09,227 --> 00:37:11,127
Results don't excuse bad behavior.

548
00:37:17,401 --> 00:37:19,198
Tell you what.

549
00:37:19,403 --> 00:37:21,701
It's clear you and I
have some issues...

550
00:37:21,872 --> 00:37:25,943
so why don't we agree just not to work
with each other anymore.

551
00:37:25,978 --> 00:37:29,447
The question isn't whether
I can work with you.

552
00:37:29,482 --> 00:37:32,644
It's how you're gonna handle
working for me.

553
00:37:38,956 --> 00:37:40,981
You?

554
00:37:42,593 --> 00:37:44,356
Me.

555
00:37:55,573 --> 00:37:57,700
Fired for cause.

556
00:37:57,842 --> 00:37:59,639
Fired for cause.

557
00:37:59,844 --> 00:38:01,512
This is bullshit!

558
00:38:01,547 --> 00:38:03,980
They're gonna have the most P.C.,
useless force in the country.

559
00:38:04,348 --> 00:38:06,373
Julien gets outed
and throws a bitch-fit...

560
00:38:06,651 --> 00:38:08,710
and we take the fall
for some friendly ribbing?

561
00:38:08,853 --> 00:38:11,222
Maybe they just don't get
your sophisticated brand of humor.

562
00:38:11,257 --> 00:38:14,521
You trying to tell me this place is better off
with him than the three of us?

563
00:38:15,026 --> 00:38:18,462
Don't put me in your corner.
I didn't deserve what I got.

564
00:38:38,816 --> 00:38:40,909
I have prepared two speeches
for this evening.

565
00:38:41,319 --> 00:38:43,583
I hope I get to use the one
in my left pocket.

566
00:38:43,721 --> 00:38:46,155
But whatever happens, win or lose...

567
00:38:46,324 --> 00:38:48,121
I thank you all.

568
00:38:48,326 --> 00:38:50,760
Your support
has been a blessing.

569
00:38:50,928 --> 00:38:53,089
To my lovely wife, Aurora...

570
00:38:53,230 --> 00:38:55,027
<i>te amo.</i>

571
00:38:55,266 --> 00:38:58,895
<i>Tu eres mi estrella brillante.</i>

572
00:39:06,977 --> 00:39:09,468
Danny.

573
00:39:09,647 --> 00:39:12,241
<i>This isn't fair.</i>

574
00:39:12,450 --> 00:39:14,350
No, it's not.

575
00:39:16,087 --> 00:39:18,487
Look, um...

576
00:39:18,656 --> 00:39:21,489
I can't tell you...

577
00:39:21,692 --> 00:39:25,150
<i>how much I... I've
learned from you.</i>

578
00:39:25,363 --> 00:39:27,695
Well, here's one last thing...

579
00:39:29,200 --> 00:39:31,395
You watch your back
around these people, okay?

580
00:40:01,132 --> 00:40:03,692
- Any sign of Armenians yet?
- Nope.

581
00:40:03,868 --> 00:40:06,132
<i>- How's our bleeder?
- Dropped him off at a clinica.</i>

582
00:40:06,337 --> 00:40:08,339
Backroom doc's sewing him up
as we speak.

583
00:40:08,374 --> 00:40:11,331
Our bleeder's gonna make it,
and he's gonna shake out of town.

584
00:40:11,609 --> 00:40:13,736
Good. Let's finish this.

585
00:40:15,579 --> 00:40:19,413
Although statewide turnout has been
somewhat lower than average...

586
00:40:19,450 --> 00:40:22,044
<i>- How deep you wanna bury this?
- Not very.</i>

587
00:40:22,453 --> 00:40:25,718
These transplants from Brighton Beach
are more beach than bright.

588
00:40:27,024 --> 00:40:28,753
<i>In the city council races...
- Hey.</i>

589
00:40:29,026 --> 00:40:31,688
<i>District three is reporting in now
with 89% of the vote.</i>

590
00:40:32,029 --> 00:40:34,589
Nah, nah. A little more clever
than that, okay?

591
00:40:34,698 --> 00:40:37,462
<i>The fifth district is still tight,
with Elliot Orlon edging closer...</i>

592
00:40:37,735 --> 00:40:41,068
<i>to incumbent
Barnard Fortain.</i>

593
00:40:41,238 --> 00:40:43,706
<i>Hey. This is good.</i>

594
00:40:43,874 --> 00:40:47,469
<i>Police Captain David Aceveda
won a tight primary race...</i>

595
00:40:47,745 --> 00:40:50,407
<i>against challenger Karen Mitchell
to become that district's...</i>

596
00:40:50,548 --> 00:40:53,949
<i>first Hispanic
Democratic candidate for council.</i>

597
00:40:54,118 --> 00:40:57,417
<i>And since the district
is 82% Democrat...</i>

598
00:40:57,555 --> 00:41:00,023
it's a safe bet that Aceveda
will soon be the first elected...

599
00:41:00,224 --> 00:41:02,124
Hispanic representative
on the council...

600
00:41:02,359 --> 00:41:04,486
from the Farmington District
of Los Angeles.

601
00:41:04,628 --> 00:41:07,256
- I thought he was gonna lose.
- He was supposed to.

602
00:41:07,465 --> 00:41:09,467
What does that mean?

603
00:41:09,502 --> 00:41:12,027
<i>It means Aceveda isn't gonna be gone
as fast as we thought.</i>

604
00:41:12,369 --> 00:41:15,497
And six months from now,
he's gonna be our boss's boss.

605
00:41:19,610 --> 00:41:22,909
<i>I can always tell
when you're lying to me.</i>

606
00:41:24,482 --> 00:41:26,973
<i>No, you always
thought you could.</i>

607
00:41:29,487 --> 00:41:33,014
What were you and your father doing
on that street today?

608
00:41:39,430 --> 00:41:41,762
There's a flower store there.

609
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:45,560
He wanted to go in
and pick up some flowers.

610
00:41:47,204 --> 00:41:49,468
For Jenny...

611
00:41:49,607 --> 00:41:51,507
<i>his fiancée.</i>

612
00:41:54,545 --> 00:41:56,647
Jeff was engaged?

613
00:41:56,682 --> 00:41:59,946
- What... Why didn't you...
- I didn't want to hurt your feelings.

614
00:42:03,254 --> 00:42:06,156
Dad told me once...

615
00:42:06,191 --> 00:42:09,319
<i>how much you liked it
when he surprised you with flowers.</i>

616
00:42:11,762 --> 00:42:14,560
He really got his life together.

617
00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:19,197
He was... happy.

618
00:42:23,741 --> 00:42:26,107
He was waiting for the right time
for us to tell you.

619
00:42:26,544 --> 00:42:28,409
Oh, what was stopping you?

620
00:42:29,847 --> 00:42:32,008
I don't know. You just...

621
00:42:34,318 --> 00:42:36,878
seem lonely...

622
00:42:37,054 --> 00:42:38,919
lately.

623
00:42:49,934 --> 00:42:52,459
I'm just glad nothing
happened to you.

624
00:42:52,636 --> 00:42:54,900
I lost my partner.
That's not nothing.

625
00:42:55,039 --> 00:42:57,405
I know. Thank you, baby.

626
00:42:57,575 --> 00:42:59,440
I hope she's okay.

627
00:42:59,476 --> 00:43:01,341
Thank you, sweetheart.
We'll do what we can for her.

628
00:43:03,781 --> 00:43:06,875
Um, let's talk
about this later, okay?

629
00:43:36,280 --> 00:43:38,976
<i>No!</i>

630
00:44:00,838 --> 00:44:03,534
I would've called. I just didn't have
the new number.

631
00:44:05,342 --> 00:44:08,470
You can't be here. Uh, tell Shane
not to come back either.

632
00:44:08,646 --> 00:44:12,673
I didn't send him.
He shouldn't have done that. Please.

633
00:44:19,723 --> 00:44:21,588
Thanks.

634
00:44:23,527 --> 00:44:25,995
We're not supposed to be
talking like this. You should go.

635
00:44:26,530 --> 00:44:29,727
I know. Uh, I won't come back again
without permission.

636
00:44:32,369 --> 00:44:35,896
I just was so worried about the kids,
spending time with them. I...

637
00:44:36,273 --> 00:44:39,970
I got lost somewhere
in all this.

638
00:44:43,781 --> 00:44:47,239
I never meant to hurt you
the way that I have.

639
00:44:49,019 --> 00:44:51,078
I'm so sorry about that.

640
00:44:55,392 --> 00:44:58,850
I want you to know,
uh...

641
00:44:59,029 --> 00:45:01,327
you're gonna be taken care of.

642
00:45:01,465 --> 00:45:03,194
The kids?

643
00:45:03,233 --> 00:45:05,098
They don't have anything
to worry about either.

644
00:45:10,774 --> 00:45:12,867
Tell 'em I love 'em.

645
00:45:13,010 --> 00:45:14,773
<i>And, uh...</i>

646
00:45:14,978 --> 00:45:18,345
call my lawyer and let him know
when a good time to see them is.

647
00:45:31,361 --> 00:45:34,660
<i>Mama!</i>

648
00:45:34,832 --> 00:45:36,697
<i>Mama!</i>

